1
00:00:11,100 --> 00:00:12,333
Damn you, Samuel.

2
00:00:12,333 --> 00:00:14,567
So you're the mastermind
behind all this.

3
00:00:14,567 --> 00:00:15,567
You're in trouble now!

4
00:00:17,433 --> 00:00:18,467
Who are you?!

5
00:00:22,567 --> 00:00:23,600
[TIRES SCREECH]

6
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:26,467
[MOTORCYCLE ENGINE REVVING]

7
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:30,167
[TIRES SCREECHING]

8
00:00:30,167 --> 00:00:31,600
- [LOUD CRASH]
- [GLASS SHATTERS]

9
00:00:38,133 --> 00:00:39,167
Samuel.

10
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:47,800
I would like to call
my first witness.

11
00:00:47,800 --> 00:00:50,600
PO2 Johnny Policarpio.

12
00:00:53,467 --> 00:00:55,300
Based on my investigation,

13
00:00:55,300 --> 00:00:58,467
King was kidnapped
by a syndicate

14
00:00:58,467 --> 00:01:00,733
led by a certain Emerson Diaz.

15
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:03,667
Before the kidnapping happened,

16
00:01:03,667 --> 00:01:07,100
Samuel Trinidad and his family
had been confronted

17
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:08,467
by an angry mob,

18
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:12,333
right in his own office
at Golden Trust Bank.

19
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:14,633
It turned chaotic,
good thing we were there.

20
00:01:14,633 --> 00:01:16,400
It wasn't just
his office they stormed,

21
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:17,800
but also his own home.

22
00:01:17,800 --> 00:01:22,167
Can you say that the child is
not safe with Samuel Trinidad?

23
00:01:22,167 --> 00:01:24,133
He's absolutely not safe
with Samuel.

24
00:01:24,133 --> 00:01:28,200
I believe that Samuel Trinidad
is a syndicate member.

25
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:30,367
Where's Papa?!

26
00:01:30,367 --> 00:01:33,000
He's currently attending
a conference.

27
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:35,300
Hello.

28
00:01:36,667 --> 00:01:38,600
Alright, I'll be on my way.

29
00:01:42,533 --> 00:01:43,833
Miss Bekkah.

30
00:01:43,833 --> 00:01:46,667
I'll use you
to find out the truth.

31
00:01:46,667 --> 00:01:49,067
How can you assure this court

32
00:01:49,067 --> 00:01:52,600
that you are fit
to be King's parent?

33
00:01:52,600 --> 00:01:55,700
I've always put
my son's needs first!

34
00:01:55,700 --> 00:01:57,367
Always!

35
00:01:57,567 --> 00:02:00,667
I'm doing everything I can
to be a good father to my son!

36
00:02:01,433 --> 00:02:04,533
At no point I've failed
to care for my son.

37
00:02:04,533 --> 00:02:06,333
I've never abandoned him.

38
00:02:06,333 --> 00:02:09,100
Everything you said was only
about the hardships

39
00:02:09,100 --> 00:02:10,367
you went through,

40
00:02:10,367 --> 00:02:13,833
without even mentioning at all
how you could put a stop

41
00:02:13,867 --> 00:02:16,400
all the dangers in King's life!

42
00:02:22,467 --> 00:02:29,400
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

43
00:02:47,633 --> 00:02:54,567
- [STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]
- [TRAFFIC NOISE]

44
00:02:58,767 --> 00:03:00,233
[ENZO] I knew it!

45
00:03:00,767 --> 00:03:02,533
You all disgust me!

46
00:03:06,733 --> 00:03:07,600
[PHONE CHIMES]

47
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:09,433
"Enzo, please reply."
"Where are you?"

48
00:03:09,433 --> 00:03:12,733
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

49
00:03:12,733 --> 00:03:16,533
[ENGINE REVVING]

50
00:03:19,467 --> 00:03:23,233
"Enzo, please reply."
"Where are you?"

51
00:03:25,267 --> 00:03:26,600
Sorry, Arissa.

52
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:33,167
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

53
00:03:33,167 --> 00:03:34,600
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

54
00:03:34,600 --> 00:03:35,800
"Enzo, what's going on?"

55
00:03:38,633 --> 00:03:40,767
- [LOLITA] His whole life...
- "Are you okay?"

56
00:03:40,767 --> 00:03:44,333
King's always been
with his father.

57
00:03:44,333 --> 00:03:46,633
Samuel, my son!

58
00:03:46,633 --> 00:03:51,600
They've been together during
all the important occasions!

59
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:55,633
And Samuel has always made sure

60
00:03:55,667 --> 00:03:59,167
that all of my grandson's needs
are provided for!

61
00:03:59,733 --> 00:04:02,867
Even when he lost his job,

62
00:04:03,667 --> 00:04:06,667
when he was blacklisted
by every single company,

63
00:04:06,667 --> 00:04:09,333
when we were struggling...

64
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:11,500
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

65
00:04:11,700 --> 00:04:15,700
Never, not once, has he
abandoned my grandson.

66
00:04:16,467 --> 00:04:18,833
In all the photos shown
of father and son...

67
00:04:18,833 --> 00:04:19,967
[LOLITA CRYING, SNIFFLING]

68
00:04:20,833 --> 00:04:22,267
where was the mother?

69
00:04:22,967 --> 00:04:24,833
Objection! Leading!

70
00:04:24,833 --> 00:04:26,267
[JUDGE SANTOS] Overruled!

71
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:29,467
This hearing is
for a custody case.

72
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:32,000
The question is relevant.
Answer the question.

73
00:04:32,867 --> 00:04:35,400
Nowhere!
She was nowhere to be found!

74
00:04:36,033 --> 00:04:40,033
When King was a baby,
she had already abandoned him!

75
00:04:40,033 --> 00:04:42,000
That makes all of it strange.

76
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:45,533
Why is she hell-bent
on taking my grandson?

77
00:04:45,533 --> 00:04:48,900
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

78
00:04:48,900 --> 00:04:51,533
Why? Was she there?

79
00:04:51,533 --> 00:04:53,900
Where was she when
he was growing up?

80
00:04:55,533 --> 00:04:59,700
Where was she when
he needed his diaper changed?

81
00:05:00,967 --> 00:05:06,000
Where was she when
he was sick and needed care?

82
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:11,367
Where was she when
he needed comforting?

83
00:05:12,067 --> 00:05:13,400
It's hard.

84
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:17,733
It's hard to entrust a child
to someone

85
00:05:17,733 --> 00:05:20,833
who abandoned him
in the first place.

86
00:05:21,700 --> 00:05:26,600
Even a stray cat
wouldn't do that!

87
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:28,900
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

88
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:30,367
[LOLITA CRYING]

89
00:05:44,933 --> 00:05:51,867
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

90
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,733
You won't get away.

91
00:05:57,733 --> 00:05:58,867
Your Honor,

92
00:05:59,733 --> 00:06:01,667
I would like to call
upon another witness

93
00:06:01,667 --> 00:06:02,833
to the witness stand.

94
00:06:02,833 --> 00:06:04,467
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

95
00:06:04,467 --> 00:06:05,767
Atty. Leah Rivera.

96
00:06:16,367 --> 00:06:17,500
[LEAH HUFFS]

97
00:06:26,933 --> 00:06:30,433
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

98
00:06:30,433 --> 00:06:32,967
Attorney, I won't beat
around the bush.

99
00:06:32,967 --> 00:06:35,967
Why did you abandon King
when he was a little boy

100
00:06:35,967 --> 00:06:37,600
and needed you the most?

101
00:06:38,933 --> 00:06:40,833
Did I abandon King?

102
00:06:41,700 --> 00:06:42,833
No!

103
00:06:42,833 --> 00:06:45,833
[MUSIC BECOMES SOMBER]

104
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:48,333
I abandoned Samuel.

105
00:06:49,833 --> 00:06:51,767
Because I wasn't happy anymore.

106
00:06:52,867 --> 00:06:56,500
I was also suffering from
postpartum depression

107
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:57,800
at the time.

108
00:06:58,567 --> 00:07:01,967
And that's the reason why
I didn't take King with me

109
00:07:01,967 --> 00:07:03,867
when I left.

110
00:07:03,867 --> 00:07:06,633
So, you are saying...

111
00:07:06,633 --> 00:07:09,167
that you are an unfit
mother, is that right?

112
00:07:09,167 --> 00:07:12,833
I was unfit to be
a mother then.

113
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:18,500
However, I have managed
to get my life in order.

114
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:20,733
I am now a successful lawyer.

115
00:07:20,733 --> 00:07:22,167
I have a good family

116
00:07:22,167 --> 00:07:24,900
and a daughter that
I raised well.

117
00:07:24,900 --> 00:07:26,033
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

118
00:07:26,033 --> 00:07:31,200
Now, I am not only a fit mother.

119
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:33,833
I am also a good mother.

120
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:38,833
My daughter, Chloe,
can prove it.

121
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:41,833
Who, by the way,
is friends with King,

122
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:45,033
before they even knew
they were siblings.

123
00:07:45,033 --> 00:07:47,833
[PAENG] So now, you're taking
him because he's grown up

124
00:07:47,867 --> 00:07:49,567
and doesn't need
constant care.

125
00:07:49,567 --> 00:07:51,033
- How convenient.
- No.

126
00:07:51,033 --> 00:07:52,567
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

127
00:07:52,567 --> 00:07:55,433
That wasn't really
my plan at first.

128
00:07:55,433 --> 00:07:58,900
But when I found out that
my son had been kidnapped,

129
00:07:58,900 --> 00:08:00,733
I was alarmed.

130
00:08:00,733 --> 00:08:04,067
Especially when I found out that
syndicates were involved.

131
00:08:04,067 --> 00:08:07,067
Because his father is
involved in the scam.

132
00:08:07,067 --> 00:08:10,967
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

133
00:08:10,967 --> 00:08:15,633
Luckily, PO2 Johnny Policarpio
saved him.

134
00:08:15,633 --> 00:08:18,467
I won't ever allow that
to happen to my son again.

135
00:08:18,467 --> 00:08:21,733
[PAENG] Were you also aware that
the group of Emerson Diaz

136
00:08:21,767 --> 00:08:23,767
attacked Enzo Rivera,

137
00:08:23,767 --> 00:08:26,133
the son of your brother-in-law,
Roldan Rivera?

138
00:08:26,133 --> 00:08:29,933
Who is also the brother of
your husband, Jacob Rivera?

139
00:08:29,933 --> 00:08:31,767
That is according
to the statement

140
00:08:31,767 --> 00:08:33,833
given by PO2 Policarpio.

141
00:08:33,833 --> 00:08:37,933
Therefore, there is
the possibility

142
00:08:37,933 --> 00:08:40,833
that the Rivera brothers are
part of the syndicate.

143
00:08:40,833 --> 00:08:41,767
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

144
00:08:41,767 --> 00:08:44,700
At that moment,
Samuel was shot as well.

145
00:08:46,067 --> 00:08:49,500
How can we be sure that
Enzo was the real target,

146
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:50,767
not Samuel?

147
00:08:50,767 --> 00:08:52,067
[PAENG]
You're right, Attorney.

148
00:08:52,067 --> 00:08:57,467
Who's to say what
Mr. Diaz's motive was

149
00:08:57,500 --> 00:08:58,467
at the time?

150
00:08:58,467 --> 00:09:02,133
But since he's dead,
we will never know.

151
00:09:02,133 --> 00:09:04,967
So even if we argue all day

152
00:09:04,967 --> 00:09:07,967
about whether
Mr. Samuel Trinidad,

153
00:09:07,967 --> 00:09:11,633
Mr. Roldan Rivera, or Mr. Jacob
Rivera is part of a syndicate,

154
00:09:11,633 --> 00:09:13,500
it's all possible.

155
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:16,133
But that doesn't mean
any of it's true.

156
00:09:16,133 --> 00:09:18,300
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

157
00:09:18,300 --> 00:09:20,800
So, tell me, Attorney.

158
00:09:20,800 --> 00:09:24,967
Are we really going to upend
a child's stable and happy life

159
00:09:24,967 --> 00:09:26,500
with his father

160
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:28,633
over mere speculations

161
00:09:28,667 --> 00:09:31,533
about Mr. Diaz's
supposed motive?

162
00:09:34,667 --> 00:09:40,800
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

163
00:09:41,833 --> 00:09:44,100
Your Honor,
no further questions.

164
00:09:48,967 --> 00:09:50,800
[JUDGE SANTOS]
I have heard enough.

165
00:09:52,067 --> 00:09:54,633
I am going to issue
my ruling tomorrow.

166
00:09:55,233 --> 00:09:56,733
However, at this point,

167
00:09:56,733 --> 00:09:58,067
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

168
00:09:58,067 --> 00:10:01,133
based on the evidence
and testimonies,

169
00:10:01,167 --> 00:10:06,033
I see no reason to alter
the child's current situation.

170
00:10:12,867 --> 00:10:19,833
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

171
00:10:35,533 --> 00:10:40,700
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

172
00:10:40,700 --> 00:10:41,900
What are you doing, Jacob?

173
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:44,567
Hey! I need to call
my wife and my daughter.

174
00:10:44,567 --> 00:10:46,133
I need to talk
to Leah and Chloe.

175
00:10:46,133 --> 00:10:47,967
Are you out of your mind?!

176
00:10:47,967 --> 00:10:51,033
I need to talk to them
and know how they're doing!

177
00:10:51,033 --> 00:10:52,067
Give that back!

178
00:10:52,067 --> 00:10:54,600
Do you think they haven't
tapped our phones?

179
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:57,533
You're only making it easier for
the Old Man to track us down!

180
00:10:58,400 --> 00:10:59,533
Give it!

181
00:11:01,567 --> 00:11:03,033
Damn that Old Man!

182
00:11:03,567 --> 00:11:04,933
Damn him!

183
00:11:04,933 --> 00:11:10,100
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

184
00:11:13,267 --> 00:11:16,133
- [MUSIC TURNS UNSETTLING]
- It's alright.

185
00:11:18,467 --> 00:11:20,267
No, Dad, it's not.

186
00:11:20,267 --> 00:11:22,633
I don't like losing
in front of you!

187
00:11:22,633 --> 00:11:24,100
I hate that!

188
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:26,167
You didn't lose.

189
00:11:26,167 --> 00:11:31,400
It just so happened that
Samuel was better today.

190
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:33,000
Forget about that.

191
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:37,133
The next best thing
for you to do is to recover

192
00:11:37,133 --> 00:11:39,133
and gather yourself

193
00:11:39,133 --> 00:11:42,400
so that the next time
you stand in a courtroom,

194
00:11:42,433 --> 00:11:47,333
you will be able to outwit,
outsmart, and outplay

195
00:11:47,333 --> 00:11:49,967
whoever you're going
to go up against.

196
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:53,467
Oh, and... don't forget.

197
00:11:53,467 --> 00:11:55,667
Remember the mistakes
you made today.

198
00:11:56,700 --> 00:11:57,967
Thanks, Dad.

199
00:11:59,133 --> 00:12:00,267
Come.

200
00:12:01,333 --> 00:12:08,267
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

201
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:18,167
I was so nervous, son.

202
00:12:18,167 --> 00:12:22,167
I thought I'd have
a heart attack.

203
00:12:22,167 --> 00:12:24,133
- Me too.
- Me three.

204
00:12:25,500 --> 00:12:26,633
Bro.

205
00:12:27,367 --> 00:12:29,233
Bro, thank you.

206
00:12:29,233 --> 00:12:33,267
Thanks to you, I won't have
to part with my son.

207
00:12:37,667 --> 00:12:39,800
- [SAMUEL] Thank you.
- [PAENG] Sure, bro.

208
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:41,767
You go ahead, Ma.

209
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:43,633
Let's go.

210
00:12:49,367 --> 00:12:50,467
Samuel!

211
00:12:58,500 --> 00:13:00,133
Dad, I have to go.

212
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:08,333
[UNSETTLING MUSIC CONTINUES]

213
00:13:10,233 --> 00:13:11,500
Congratulations, Samuel.

214
00:13:12,567 --> 00:13:13,667
Thank you, sir.

215
00:13:15,233 --> 00:13:16,733
I have fixed your problem.

216
00:13:21,533 --> 00:13:23,067
Judge Santos.

217
00:13:24,433 --> 00:13:26,567
- Leah.
- What happened?

218
00:13:26,567 --> 00:13:28,900
You just suddenly changed
your ruling?

219
00:13:28,900 --> 00:13:34,567
Leah, you are one of the
brightest lawyers I know.

220
00:13:34,567 --> 00:13:36,600
You should know,
of all people,

221
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:39,400
that the court chooses
what's best for the kids.

222
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:42,500
Especially in cases
like emergency custody.

223
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:48,200
Did Samuel Trinidad talk to you?

224
00:13:49,533 --> 00:13:50,833
Did he threaten you?

225
00:13:56,167 --> 00:14:03,133
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

226
00:14:04,500 --> 00:14:06,900
Tell me the truth,
Judge Santos.

227
00:14:06,900 --> 00:14:09,800
How dare you insinuate
such things?

228
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:14,267
I can have you disbarred
because of this.

229
00:14:20,633 --> 00:14:23,767
I cannot afford for you
to be distracted

230
00:14:23,767 --> 00:14:27,233
because I'm assigning you
an important mission.

231
00:14:28,833 --> 00:14:30,233
What is it, sir?

232
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:35,600
I want you to hunt down
the Rivera brothers.

233
00:14:39,633 --> 00:14:41,833
Do you have any
problem with that?

234
00:14:41,833 --> 00:14:48,767
[DARK MUSIC CONTINUES]

235
00:14:52,967 --> 00:14:54,667
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

236
00:14:54,667 --> 00:14:55,667
Pido!

237
00:14:56,500 --> 00:14:57,500
Boss.

238
00:14:57,500 --> 00:14:58,533
Where's Pido?!

239
00:14:58,533 --> 00:14:59,667
He's not here, boss.

240
00:15:01,500 --> 00:15:02,667
That's not good!

241
00:15:06,733 --> 00:15:08,000
[PHONE CHIMES]

242
00:15:10,567 --> 00:15:12,833
[UNSETTLING MUSIC STING]

243
00:15:12,833 --> 00:15:13,867
What is this?

244
00:15:17,533 --> 00:15:19,000
Pido?!

245
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:22,033
What the hell?!
Who's responsible for this?!

246
00:15:25,167 --> 00:15:26,800
[PHONE RINGS]

247
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:31,067
[FERDIE] Hello, Congressman.

248
00:15:31,067 --> 00:15:34,567
So? Did you like my gift?

249
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,567
Damn you, Pastor.

250
00:15:37,567 --> 00:15:39,667
Don't touch the money,

251
00:15:39,667 --> 00:15:41,033
I need it!

252
00:15:41,233 --> 00:15:42,800
Oh, where are you
going to use it?

253
00:15:43,500 --> 00:15:45,267
[FERDIE] For the election?
[CHUCKLES]

254
00:15:45,267 --> 00:15:47,900
Are you running for Congress
again or for senator?

255
00:15:49,900 --> 00:15:51,900
What are you going
to do now, Congressman?

256
00:15:51,900 --> 00:15:54,067
You don't have money
to buy votes anymore!

257
00:15:54,067 --> 00:15:56,833
Damn you, Pastor! Damn you!

258
00:15:56,833 --> 00:15:58,767
You're a monster!

259
00:15:58,767 --> 00:15:59,967
Shh!

260
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:02,067
Don't say bad words.

261
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:05,533
You don't want
to go to hell, do you?

262
00:16:05,533 --> 00:16:09,567
[CACKLING]

263
00:16:10,133 --> 00:16:12,633
[HUFFING]

264
00:16:12,633 --> 00:16:17,967
The devil
won't accept you in hell.

265
00:16:17,967 --> 00:16:21,100
Because you might steal
his throne.

266
00:16:21,733 --> 00:16:24,167
[ABEL]
 You liar, pervert pastor!

267
00:16:24,767 --> 00:16:27,633
Damn you! I hope you die!

268
00:16:27,633 --> 00:16:34,600
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

269
00:16:36,267 --> 00:16:43,200
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

270
00:16:57,133 --> 00:16:58,833
- Sir.
- Hmm?

271
00:16:58,833 --> 00:17:01,267
You have checked
this evidence several times.

272
00:17:02,833 --> 00:17:06,600
What if our dumb colleagues
missed something?

273
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:11,000
What if a syndicate group
is involved again?

274
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:12,800
I don't want the case
to be whitewashed.

275
00:17:15,100 --> 00:17:17,267
If Trinidad really has anything
to do with it,

276
00:17:17,267 --> 00:17:18,767
I want to catch him right away.

277
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:21,933
So I can help my sister

278
00:17:21,933 --> 00:17:23,833
have full custody
of my nephew King.

279
00:17:24,367 --> 00:17:25,533
Wow!

280
00:17:25,533 --> 00:17:28,700
Sir, should I call you
Brother of the Year?

281
00:17:28,700 --> 00:17:29,733
[SCOFFS]

282
00:17:35,100 --> 00:17:36,967
The bomb has a detonator, right?

283
00:17:36,967 --> 00:17:38,133
Yes, sir.

284
00:17:40,800 --> 00:17:45,033
Where should you be
in order to activate it?

285
00:17:45,033 --> 00:17:52,000
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

286
00:17:58,233 --> 00:18:00,033
I feel like
I've seen this before.

287
00:18:04,233 --> 00:18:10,233
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

288
00:18:10,233 --> 00:18:12,033
[EXPLOSION]

289
00:18:15,833 --> 00:18:17,300
[SCREAMING]

290
00:18:23,233 --> 00:18:24,667
[DIEGO GROANS]

291
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:28,067
[DIEGO, SAMUEL GRUNTING]

292
00:18:29,667 --> 00:18:31,667
The old man rigged
my case with Leah

293
00:18:31,767 --> 00:18:34,033
so I'd hunt down the Riveras.

294
00:18:34,900 --> 00:18:36,567
He deceived his daughter
just for that?

295
00:18:36,733 --> 00:18:37,867
Wait, wait.

296
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:41,033
W-What? Does that mean
I didn't really win earlier?

297
00:18:41,200 --> 00:18:43,467
No, bro.
You were amazing earlier.

298
00:18:43,567 --> 00:18:45,033
You really won.

299
00:18:45,200 --> 00:18:47,500
The Old Man probably just
gave Judge Santos a little push

300
00:18:47,600 --> 00:18:48,700
so he'd rule in your favor.

301
00:18:48,867 --> 00:18:51,967
Of course! I did my best.
I prepared a lot for that case.

302
00:18:52,067 --> 00:18:54,500
Samuel, that means
that's how important

303
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:55,867
the mission he gave to you is.

304
00:18:56,067 --> 00:18:58,933
No, no. I can't do it.

305
00:19:00,633 --> 00:19:03,100
I can fool them,
stir up trouble,

306
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:05,367
pit them against each other
to take down Bakunawa--

307
00:19:05,467 --> 00:19:06,500
I can do all that, but...

308
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:08,933
But kill them?

309
00:19:09,967 --> 00:19:13,167
I can't do that,
no matter how evil they are.

310
00:19:13,267 --> 00:19:16,833
Samuel, you're not
a civilian anymore.

311
00:19:16,933 --> 00:19:18,833
And you chose this mission.

312
00:19:18,933 --> 00:19:22,000
So you need to make
a difficult decision

313
00:19:22,100 --> 00:19:23,500
even if it's against your will!

314
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:25,000
No, Colonel.

315
00:19:25,100 --> 00:19:26,567
No, there must be other ways.

316
00:19:27,700 --> 00:19:29,167
Anything!

317
00:19:29,300 --> 00:19:31,433
When will we raid
the scam warehouse?

318
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:35,100
We need to be careful.
I'm still vetting people.

319
00:19:35,267 --> 00:19:36,633
And Matthias? Is he awake?

320
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:37,767
He's still in a coma.

321
00:19:37,933 --> 00:19:40,467
The problem is,
Mael can't open the laptop!

322
00:19:41,467 --> 00:19:44,133
The encryption's too strong.
He's like the God of Codes.

323
00:19:44,300 --> 00:19:46,233
Bro, I need a few more days.

324
00:19:46,333 --> 00:19:47,933
What do we do now?

325
00:19:48,100 --> 00:19:49,533
We'll find another way.

326
00:19:50,433 --> 00:19:53,733
I can't do what
the Old Man ordered. I can't.

327
00:19:53,833 --> 00:19:55,933
But, bro, what if he
loses trust in you?

328
00:19:56,100 --> 00:19:58,800
Then I need to show him
that I'm doing what he wants.

329
00:19:58,967 --> 00:20:00,433
That's what I'll do for now.

330
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:04,567
By the time he finds out
I'm deceiving him,

331
00:20:04,667 --> 00:20:06,267
it will be too late.

332
00:20:07,467 --> 00:20:11,467
Once we're all ready,
we'll raid the scam warehouse.

333
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:14,967
But I can't kill a person!

334
00:20:15,100 --> 00:20:22,100
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

335
00:20:39,067 --> 00:20:46,133
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

336
00:20:48,033 --> 00:20:50,100
Enzo, why didn't you pick up?
You made me so worried!

337
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:52,667
I don't want you and Samuel
to stop me.

338
00:20:52,800 --> 00:20:53,967
What are you doing?

339
00:20:54,067 --> 00:20:55,033
Let me go!

340
00:20:55,200 --> 00:20:56,133
Please don't do this.

341
00:20:56,233 --> 00:20:57,333
Think of our friendship.

342
00:20:57,500 --> 00:21:00,767
You ruined it when you
took your brother's side!

343
00:21:00,867 --> 00:21:02,333
I have to help Enzo. Please!

344
00:21:02,467 --> 00:21:03,800
I was supposed to leave.

345
00:21:03,900 --> 00:21:06,333
My son and I won't be able
to make up because of you!

346
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:10,000
This happened because of
your selfishness and greed!

347
00:21:10,167 --> 00:21:12,067
Roldan's son
is in danger.

348
00:21:12,233 --> 00:21:14,567
This is Armagedon.
